## Soundness Properties

> A process is sound if and only if: (1) it is deadlock-free, (2) every action eventually completes (liveness), and (3) all resources are bounded.

| Property | Guarantee | Key Rule |
|----------|-----------|----------|
| **Deadlock Freedom** | No state where all processes wait indefinitely | Every blocking op has timeout + fallback |
| **Liveness** | Every started action eventually completes | All loops bounded; all state machines terminating |
| **Boundedness** | No unbounded resource growth | Queues, caches, memory have explicit limits |

