## WvdA Verification Workflow

### Step 1: Static Analysis
- [ ] Code review: identify all blocking operations
- [ ] Check: every wait/lock has timeout_ms documented
- [ ] Check: no cyclic resource dependencies

### Step 2: Formal Model
- [ ] Model as Petri net or finite state machine
- [ ] Verify deadlock-freedom (no dead transitions)
- [ ] Verify safety (1-bounded places)
- [ ] Verify liveness (every transition can fire from initial marking)

### Step 3: Runtime Verification
- [ ] Chaos tests: inject delays, timeouts, network failures
- [ ] Load tests: verify boundedness under peak load
- [ ] Measure: timeout distribution, queue depths, memory growth

### Step 4: Merge Gate
- [ ] All three soundness properties verified
- [ ] Chaos test results with timeout distribution
- [ ] Load test results showing bounded growth

